WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.835 --> 00:00:03.254
Viserys Targaryen:
I. Viserys Targaryen.

2
00:00:03.796 --> 00:00:05.757
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.

3
00:00:06.007 --> 00:00:10.678
do hereby name
Rhaenyra Targaryen heir...

4
00:00:12.180 --> 00:00:13.639
<i>to the Iron Throne.</i>

5
00:00:15.016 --> 00:00:18.186
♪ (foreboding music plays)

6
00:00:19.645 --> 00:00:23.607
The King will die.
and if Rhaenyra succeeds him.

7
00:00:23.608 --> 00:00:25.193
<i>war will follow.</i>

8
00:00:25.318 --> 00:00:26.818
<i>The realm will not accept her.</i>

9
00:00:26.819 --> 00:00:28.321
<i>And to secure her claim.</i>

10
00:00:28.446 --> 00:00:30.990
<i>she'll have to put
your children to the sword.</i>

11
00:00:31.699 --> 00:00:33.283
Alicent Hightower:
<i>Criston Cole will be named</i>

12
00:00:33.284 --> 00:00:35.369
<i>Lord Commander
of the Kingsguard.</i>

13
00:00:36.120 --> 00:00:38.206
<i>I trust you and your loyalty.</i>

14
00:00:38.331 --> 00:00:39.707
I will not fail you.

15
00:00:40.208 --> 00:00:41.375
I need you. Uncle.

16
00:00:41.834 --> 00:00:45.171
(speaking in High Valyrian)

17
00:00:47.632 --> 00:00:48.632
Viserys: Rhaenyra...

18
00:00:48.633 --> 00:00:49.674
(thunder)

19
00:00:49.675 --> 00:00:50.802
You wanted to know.

20
00:00:51.177 --> 00:00:52.845
Aegon's dream.

21
00:00:53.513 --> 00:00:54.638
The Song of Ice...

22
00:00:54.639 --> 00:00:55.680
(thunder)

23
00:00:55.681 --> 00:00:56.724
...and Fire.

24
00:00:57.225 --> 00:00:59.060
The Prince That Was Promised.

25
00:00:59.394 --> 00:01:01.229
<i>- Aegon.</i>
- Alicent: <i>Our son.</i>

26
00:01:01.354 --> 00:01:02.688
I understand. my King.

27
00:01:06.567 --> 00:01:07.693
The King is dead.

28
00:01:08.528 --> 00:01:10.362
Arryk Cargyll:
<i>Aegon is unfit to rule.</i>

29
00:01:10.363 --> 00:01:12.531
You tolerated the Prince's
proclivities for years.

30
00:01:12.532 --> 00:01:14.242
Because it was my sworn duty.
Arryk.

31
00:01:14.409 --> 00:01:17.577
When you install your grandson
on the throne.

32
00:01:17.578 --> 00:01:20.748
<i>remember it was me
who put him there.</i>

33
00:01:21.249 --> 00:01:22.708
Otto Hightower:
<i>I will remember.</i>

34
00:01:24.252 --> 00:01:26.378
speaker:
<i>All hail His Grace!</i>

35
00:01:26.379 --> 00:01:28.004
You are usurping the throne.

36
00:01:28.005 --> 00:01:30.048
speaker:
<i>Lord of the Seven Kingdoms...</i>

37
00:01:30.049 --> 00:01:31.384
She will never bend the knee.

38
00:01:31.551 --> 00:01:33.844
speaker:
<i>...and Protector of the Realm.</i>

39
00:01:33.845 --> 00:01:37.724
- (commotion)
- (Meleys roars)

40
00:01:39.058 --> 00:01:41.853
(Meleys screeches)

41
00:01:42.395 --> 00:01:45.440
A war is like to be fought
over this treachery. to be sure.

42
00:01:46.107 --> 00:01:47.775
I swear to ward the Queen.

43
00:01:47.900 --> 00:01:51.112
Otto: <i>Alicent has not forgotten
the love you had for each other.</i>

44
00:01:51.237 --> 00:01:53.071
<i>No blood need be spilled.</i>

45
00:01:53.072 --> 00:01:55.742
<i>so the realm can carry on
in peace.</i>

46
00:01:56.075 --> 00:01:58.618
That girl destroys everything
she touches.

47
00:01:58.619 --> 00:02:00.579
Rhaenys Targaryen: <i>Every
man standing 'round the Painted Table</i>

48
00:02:00.580 --> 00:02:02.123
<i>urges her to plunge the realm
into war.</i>

49
00:02:02.248 --> 00:02:03.707
Daemon Targaryen:
<i>The enemy have declared war.</i>

50
00:02:03.708 --> 00:02:05.418
What are you gonna do about it?

51
00:02:06.377 --> 00:02:09.296
You have the full support
of our fleet and house.

52
00:02:09.297 --> 00:02:11.214
Rhaenyra Targaryen:
<i>Prince Jacaerys will fly north</i>

53
00:02:11.215 --> 00:02:12.300
<i>to Winterfell.</i>

54
00:02:12.717 --> 00:02:15.470
<i>Prince Lucerys will fly south
to Storm's End.</i>

55
00:02:15.970 --> 00:02:19.807
<i>We must remind these lords
of the oaths they swore.</i>

56
00:02:20.933 --> 00:02:22.727
I want you to put out your eye.

57
00:02:22.935 --> 00:02:23.811
No.

58
00:02:24.062 --> 00:02:27.272
Give me your eye
or I will take it. bastard!

59
00:02:27.273 --> 00:02:29.317
♪ (music continues) ♪

60
00:02:31.611 --> 00:02:33.488
- (Vhagar growls)
- (Arrax yelps)

61
00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:35.490
Aemond Targaryen: <i>No!</i>

62
00:02:38.659 --> 00:02:40.495
Rhaenys: <i>The Greens
are coming for you. Rhaenyra.</i>

63
00:02:41.287 --> 00:02:42.663
♪ (music fades out)

64
00:02:50.296 --> 00:02:53.466
(epic theme playing)

65
00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:01.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

66
00:03:42.557 --> 00:03:47.019
♪

67
00:04:29.395 --> 00:04:31.564
(theme concludes)

68
00:04:38.738 --> 00:04:40.655
(birds chirping)

69
00:04:40.656 --> 00:04:43.408
(ambient nature sounds)

70
00:04:43.409 --> 00:04:46.704
(light music playing)

71
00:04:48.289 --> 00:04:50.291
(raven caws)

72
00:04:57.548 --> 00:04:59.467
♪

73
00:04:59.592 --> 00:05:01.761
(wind blowing)

74
00:05:07.892 --> 00:05:11.104
speaker:
<i>Duty is sacrifice.</i>

75
00:05:12.146 --> 00:05:14.440
<i>It eclipses all things.</i>

76
00:05:14.565 --> 00:05:16.275
<i>even blood.</i>

77
00:05:17.777 --> 00:05:21.114
<i>All men of honor
must pay its price.</i>

78
00:05:25.451 --> 00:05:29.121
<i>The North owes a great duty
to the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

79
00:05:29.122 --> 00:05:31.915
<i>- One older than any oath.</i>
- (dog barking)

80
00:05:31.916 --> 00:05:33.835
<i>Since the days of the First Men.</i>

81
00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:36.420
<i>we have stood as guardians</i>

82
00:05:36.421 --> 00:05:38.297
<i>against the cold and the dark.</i>

83
00:05:39.757 --> 00:05:41.467
<i>Through its long tradition.</i>

84
00:05:41.592 --> 00:05:43.677
<i>the Night's Watch
cultivated its strength</i>

85
00:05:43.678 --> 00:05:45.138
<i>from doomed men</i>

86
00:05:45.263 --> 00:05:47.889
<i>who had their life
as their only possession.</i>

87
00:05:47.890 --> 00:05:50.726
<i>But my ancestor. Torrhen Stark.</i>

88
00:05:50.727 --> 00:05:52.811
<i>began a tradition
by making an offering</i>

89
00:05:52.812 --> 00:05:55.148
<i>at the onset of winter:</i>

90
00:05:55.273 --> 00:05:57.607
<i>one in 10 men from our household</i>

91
00:05:57.608 --> 00:06:00.945
<i>was to be chosen
to fortify the Watch.</i>

92
00:06:03.531 --> 00:06:08.785
<i>This is not a sentence
but an honor.</i>

93
00:06:08.786 --> 00:06:12.874
<i>A duty embraced by all
who serve the North.</i>

94
00:06:12.999 --> 00:06:15.292
<i>Even by mine own kin.</i>

95
00:06:15.293 --> 00:06:17.503
♪

96
00:06:17.628 --> 00:06:20.381
(wind blowing)

97
00:06:20.506 --> 00:06:23.009
<i>The North must stand ready.</i>

98
00:06:24.343 --> 00:06:25.761
<i>Winter is coming.</i>

99
00:06:25.762 --> 00:06:27.971
Coming?
What is this. then.

100
00:06:27.972 --> 00:06:29.973
that falls from the skies
and shivers my bones?

101
00:06:29.974 --> 00:06:33.769
This is only a late
summer snow. my prince.

102
00:06:33.770 --> 00:06:36.188
In winter. it will
cover all you see.

103
00:06:36.189 --> 00:06:39.775
and all memories of
warmth will be forgotten.

104
00:06:39.776 --> 00:06:41.985
It pleases me to think
that over a century ago

105
00:06:41.986 --> 00:06:44.989
our ancestors treated
in this very place.

106
00:06:46.032 --> 00:06:48.201
The Conqueror
and the King in the North.

107
00:06:49.869 --> 00:06:51.579
You. at least. had the mercy

108
00:06:51.704 --> 00:06:53.873
not to threaten me
with your dragon.

109
00:06:53.998 --> 00:06:56.375
(lift creaks loudly)

110
00:07:00.254 --> 00:07:02.215
(distant shouting)

111
00:07:02.340 --> 00:07:03.965
My prince.

112
00:07:03.966 --> 00:07:06.219
- My lord.
- My lord.

113
00:07:07.095 --> 00:07:08.303
M'lord.

114
00:07:08.304 --> 00:07:10.598
Surely the great Torrhen Stark

115
00:07:10.723 --> 00:07:13.558
would've sooner died
than bent the knee.

116
00:07:13.559 --> 00:07:14.727
Unless he believed the Conqueror

117
00:07:14.852 --> 00:07:17.230
could bring unity
to the Seven Kingdoms.

118
00:07:18.523 --> 00:07:20.065
You are right in that.

119
00:07:20.066 --> 00:07:22.527
That unity is now threatened.

120
00:07:23.236 --> 00:07:25.904
The realm will soon
tear itself apart...

121
00:07:25.905 --> 00:07:26.906
if men do not remember

122
00:07:27.031 --> 00:07:28.741
the oath sworn to King Viserys

123
00:07:29.075 --> 00:07:31.201
and to his rightful heir.

124
00:07:31.202 --> 00:07:34.872
Starks do not forget
their oaths. my prince.

125
00:07:35.248 --> 00:07:37.707
But you must know
that my gaze is

126
00:07:37.708 --> 00:07:40.253
forever torn between
north and south.

127
00:07:41.254 --> 00:07:44.632
In winter. my duty to
the Wall is even more dire

128
00:07:44.757 --> 00:07:46.467
than the one I owe
to King's Landing.

129
00:07:46.592 --> 00:07:48.677
I need my men here.

130
00:07:48.678 --> 00:07:49.886
Whilst your men guard against

131
00:07:49.887 --> 00:07:51.680
wildlings and weather.

132
00:07:51.681 --> 00:07:54.475
the Hightowers plan
to usurp the throne.

133
00:07:55.143 --> 00:07:57.478
If my mother is
to defend her claim

134
00:07:57.603 --> 00:07:58.729
to hold the realm united.

135
00:07:58.730 --> 00:08:00.230
she needs an army.

136
00:08:00.231 --> 00:08:01.065
War is coming

137
00:08:01.066 --> 00:08:03.109
to the whole
of the realm. my lord.

138
00:08:03.234 --> 00:08:06.279
We cannot wage it without
the support of the North.

139
00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:09.282
(wind blowing)

140
00:08:14.120 --> 00:08:16.079
My father brought King Jaehaerys

141
00:08:16.080 --> 00:08:18.499
and Queen Alysanne
to see the Wall.

142
00:08:19.125 --> 00:08:21.793
His Grace stood
at this very outlook

143
00:08:21.794 --> 00:08:23.838
and watched as their dragons.

144
00:08:23.963 --> 00:08:26.466
the greatest power in the world.

145
00:08:26.591 --> 00:08:28.593
refused to cross it.

146
00:08:30.094 --> 00:08:31.887
Do you think my ancestors built

147
00:08:31.888 --> 00:08:33.930
a 700-foot wall of ice

148
00:08:33.931 --> 00:08:36.976
to keep out snow and savages?

149
00:08:37.101 --> 00:08:39.145
What does it keep out?

150
00:08:41.147 --> 00:08:42.481
Death.

151
00:08:42.482 --> 00:08:45.943
(light. tense music playing)

152
00:08:50.281 --> 00:08:52.574
I have thousands of graybeards

153
00:08:52.575 --> 00:08:54.951
who've already seen
too many winters.

154
00:08:54.952 --> 00:08:58.455
They are...
well-honed.

155
00:08:58.456 --> 00:09:00.833
So they're old?

156
00:09:00.958 --> 00:09:03.752
I can ready them
to march at once.

157
00:09:03.753 --> 00:09:05.046
If your graybeards can fight.

158
00:09:05.171 --> 00:09:07.506
the queen will have them.

159
00:09:07.507 --> 00:09:09.424
They will fight hard.

160
00:09:09.425 --> 00:09:11.010
Like Northerners.

161
00:09:11.135 --> 00:09:12.177
Stark captain:
My lord?

162
00:09:12.178 --> 00:09:15.515
- (footsteps approaching)
- A raven's arrived.

163
00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:17.517
Urgent news from Dragonstone.

164
00:09:30.405 --> 00:09:33.408
(tense music playing)

165
00:09:37.245 --> 00:09:38.996
(roars)

166
00:09:45.336 --> 00:09:47.046
(Meleys roars)

167
00:09:51.175 --> 00:09:53.177
(Rhaenys speaks High Valyrian)

168
00:09:53.428 --> 00:09:55.680
(dragonkeeper speaks
High Valyrian)

169
00:09:59.934 --> 00:10:03.438
Take your mount again.
We're flying out.

170
00:10:06.023 --> 00:10:09.610
I alone patrol over
a hundred miles of open sea.

171
00:10:09.736 --> 00:10:12.572
endlessly. to hold the blockade.

172
00:10:13.281 --> 00:10:17.076
Meleys must gorge
and rest. as must I.

173
00:10:18.286 --> 00:10:20.871
- We're going to King's Landing.
- To what end?

174
00:10:20.872 --> 00:10:22.330
Killing Vhagar.

175
00:10:22.331 --> 00:10:25.375
I cannot face that
hoary old bitch alone.

176
00:10:25.376 --> 00:10:27.002
With my dragon
and yours together.

177
00:10:27.003 --> 00:10:29.713
we can kill Vhagar
and her rider.

178
00:10:29.714 --> 00:10:31.257
Make it a son for a son.

179
00:10:33.259 --> 00:10:35.970
- Was this the queen's command?
- The queen remains absent.

180
00:10:36.095 --> 00:10:38.013
I should be at
Harrenhal bending knees.

181
00:10:38.014 --> 00:10:40.767
but I must instead remain
here to wage her war.

182
00:10:40.892 --> 00:10:43.311
Or perhaps. more simply.
to await her return.

183
00:10:43.436 --> 00:10:46.814
She has been gone for days.
Too long. She is exposed.

184
00:10:46.939 --> 00:10:49.066
- She is grieving.
- The mother grieves

185
00:10:49.067 --> 00:10:51.611
as the queen shirks her duties.

186
00:10:53.404 --> 00:10:57.741
It was a raven that brought
me news of Laena's death.

187
00:10:57.742 --> 00:11:00.952
I existed for weeks
in torment...

188
00:11:00.953 --> 00:11:04.123
refusing to believe
what I'd been told.

189
00:11:05.792 --> 00:11:08.710
It was only when I saw my
daughter's mortal remains

190
00:11:08.711 --> 00:11:11.297
that I could begin to mourn her.

191
00:11:13.424 --> 00:11:17.303
A raven has told Rhaenyra
that her son is dead.

192
00:11:18.262 --> 00:11:19.805
She needs to know it
for certain.

193
00:11:19.806 --> 00:11:21.849
She was a fool to go alone.

194
00:11:22.475 --> 00:11:24.143
What if Aemond were
to happen upon her?

195
00:11:24.268 --> 00:11:26.312
Then I would pity Aemond.

196
00:11:28.815 --> 00:11:30.942
The queen was wise
to recuse herself.

197
00:11:31.818 --> 00:11:37.280
She has not acted on the vengeful
impulse that others might have.

198
00:11:37.281 --> 00:11:40.450
If you'd have acted when
you had the chance...

199
00:11:40.451 --> 00:11:43.454
Aegon's line would
be extinguished.

200
00:11:44.664 --> 00:11:47.125
And Luke would be alive.

201
00:11:54.006 --> 00:11:55.717
Fly with me.

202
00:11:56.342 --> 00:12:00.179
- It is a command.
- Would that you were the king.

203
00:12:03.683 --> 00:12:06.643
(solemn music playing)

204
00:12:06.644 --> 00:12:08.688
(dragons calling)

205
00:12:19.574 --> 00:12:22.577
♪

206
00:12:30.376 --> 00:12:33.713
(workers chattering. shouting)

207
00:12:37.216 --> 00:12:39.427
(animals chattering)

208
00:12:51.397 --> 00:12:53.733
(people greeting Corlys)

209
00:13:09.916 --> 00:13:11.250
M'lord.

210
00:13:13.628 --> 00:13:17.256
It's a marvel she was able to
return from the Stepstones at all.

211
00:13:19.384 --> 00:13:21.219
Barely done. but done.

212
00:13:21.594 --> 00:13:25.306
Seven more ships put out to sea
this morn' to fortify the blockade.

213
00:13:25.431 --> 00:13:27.849
The Gullet is vast. and we're
not like to have the numbers

214
00:13:27.850 --> 00:13:30.269
to cover all that open water.

215
00:13:32.647 --> 00:13:34.689
Corlys Velaryon:
I must have my ship back at sea

216
00:13:34.690 --> 00:13:35.775
to lead the effort.

217
00:13:35.900 --> 00:13:38.778
Alyn of Hull: It'll be many
weeks yet. I'd wager.

218
00:13:40.446 --> 00:13:41.989
But I'll have a word
with my brother...

219
00:13:42.824 --> 00:13:46.452
to see what reinforcements
the shipwrights can muster.

220
00:13:56.129 --> 00:13:58.923
The smithy delivered
this earlier.

221
00:14:01.008 --> 00:14:02.427
M'lord?

222
00:14:10.768 --> 00:14:14.147
I had this commissioned
for Prince Lucerys.

223
00:14:15.940 --> 00:14:19.152
I was very sorry to hear
about your heir's death.

224
00:14:19.610 --> 00:14:21.821
'Twas the blackest
of treacheries.

225
00:14:24.824 --> 00:14:29.661
Pardon. m'lord. if it'll
please you. much to do.

226
00:14:29.662 --> 00:14:31.038
They tell me that
you are the one

227
00:14:31.164 --> 00:14:33.374
that dragged my body
out of the sea.

228
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:40.381
It was only my duty.

229
00:14:44.677 --> 00:14:47.972
I am indebted to you. Alyn.

230
00:15:00.026 --> 00:15:03.195
(light. tense music playing)

231
00:15:03.196 --> 00:15:05.990
(ambient nature sounds)

232
00:15:14.082 --> 00:15:16.334
♪

233
00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:23.716
- (indistinct chatter)
- (horse neighs)

234
00:15:25.218 --> 00:15:27.220
(soldier shouting)

235
00:15:27.387 --> 00:15:29.347
Mind your posts!

236
00:15:32.058 --> 00:15:34.227
Keep your focus. men!

237
00:15:37.563 --> 00:15:40.066
- guard 1 (shouts): Dragon!
- guard 2 (shouts): Dragon!

238
00:15:40.191 --> 00:15:41.567
Arm the scorpion!

239
00:15:41.692 --> 00:15:44.237
guard 1 (shouts):
Arm the scorpion!

240
00:15:45.696 --> 00:15:48.198
Approaching from the southeast!

241
00:15:48.199 --> 00:15:49.409
Get around!

242
00:15:49.534 --> 00:15:51.577
- (scorpion creaking)
- (guard shouting)

243
00:15:54.080 --> 00:15:55.497
guard (shouts):
Scorpion ready!

244
00:15:55.498 --> 00:15:58.417
- Arryk Cargyll (shouts): Halt!
- guard (shouts): Halt!

245
00:15:58.418 --> 00:16:00.753
(Vhagar grumbles)

246
00:16:00.878 --> 00:16:02.170
Stand down. it's Vhagar!

247
00:16:02.171 --> 00:16:04.089
guard 2:
Stand down!

248
00:16:04.090 --> 00:16:06.050
guard 1:
Standing down!

249
00:16:10.263 --> 00:16:12.473
(scorpion creaking)

250
00:16:14.308 --> 00:16:16.269
(Vhagar grumbles)

251
00:16:16.394 --> 00:16:18.604
(quiet chatter)

252
00:16:32.952 --> 00:16:34.787
Where is Jaehaerys?

253
00:16:36.122 --> 00:16:38.291
Attending his lessons.

254
00:16:38.958 --> 00:16:40.460
And those are where?

255
00:16:40.585 --> 00:16:42.085
What do you need of him?

256
00:16:42.086 --> 00:16:44.212
Taking him to the small council.

257
00:16:44.213 --> 00:16:45.255
He'll be king one day.

258
00:16:45.256 --> 00:16:47.258
He must begin his instruction.

259
00:16:47.592 --> 00:16:49.969
What if he does not
want to be king?

260
00:16:51.095 --> 00:16:52.304
(whispers)
Where is he?

261
00:16:52.305 --> 00:16:53.473
The library.

262
00:16:53.765 --> 00:16:56.476
You must not
interrupt his custom.

263
00:17:03.149 --> 00:17:04.817
I'm afraid.

264
00:17:07.195 --> 00:17:08.362
Don't be.

265
00:17:08.988 --> 00:17:11.907
They'd be fools to come
with Vhagar protecting the city.

266
00:17:11.908 --> 00:17:13.993
Not the dragons.

267
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:16.037
The rats.

268
00:17:24.837 --> 00:17:27.632
The queen is
an enduring mystery...

269
00:17:28.174 --> 00:17:29.717
is she not?

270
00:17:34.389 --> 00:17:36.641
(birds chirping)

271
00:17:39.018 --> 00:17:41.020
(heavy breathing)

272
00:17:42.188 --> 00:17:44.399
(quiet moaning)

273
00:17:54.033 --> 00:17:56.035
(birds cawing)

274
00:18:03.418 --> 00:18:05.420
There's a chill in the air.

275
00:18:09.507 --> 00:18:11.884
Summer is well
and truly through.

276
00:18:13.052 --> 00:18:16.097
We are expected at the
small council. Your Grace.

277
00:18:31.904 --> 00:18:33.406
We cannot.

278
00:18:33.948 --> 00:18:35.116
Again.

279
00:18:38.119 --> 00:18:39.871
Yes. Your Grace.

280
00:18:44.417 --> 00:18:46.586
If you wouldn't mind?

281
00:18:50.757 --> 00:18:53.926
(light music playing)

282
00:19:04.437 --> 00:19:06.606
(dog whimpers)

283
00:19:07.815 --> 00:19:09.817
♪

284
00:19:19.285 --> 00:19:21.953
- Tyland Lannister: Your Grace.
- Alicent Hightower: Good day.

285
00:19:21.954 --> 00:19:23.998
♪

286
00:19:26.125 --> 00:19:28.503
Aegon Targaryen: Hello! Jaehaerys
must learn the ways of the court

287
00:19:28.628 --> 00:19:30.545
if he is to rule
one day. (laughs)

288
00:19:30.546 --> 00:19:32.965
Up we go.
(laughs)

289
00:19:33.800 --> 00:19:36.259
Good morrow. my lords.

290
00:19:36.260 --> 00:19:37.512
Mother.

291
00:19:39.472 --> 00:19:41.098
What news?

292
00:19:41.099 --> 00:19:43.725
Otto Hightower: Our letters
to the Vale and to the North

293
00:19:43.726 --> 00:19:46.145
continue to go unanswered.

294
00:19:46.813 --> 00:19:47.814
Cunts.

295
00:19:49.315 --> 00:19:51.608
Otto:
The Stormlands should be ours

296
00:19:51.609 --> 00:19:53.361
after Prince Aemond's
marriage pact

297
00:19:53.486 --> 00:19:55.570
to the Lady Floris Baratheon.

298
00:19:55.571 --> 00:19:57.739
I anticipate their
sworn declaration.

299
00:19:57.740 --> 00:20:01.827
(sighs) My brother is raising
the strength of the West

300
00:20:01.828 --> 00:20:05.122
to mass at the
Golden Tooth. but we...

301
00:20:05.123 --> 00:20:06.665
Yeah. thank you. my prince.

302
00:20:06.666 --> 00:20:09.168
That's. that's very helpful.

303
00:20:09.293 --> 00:20:10.627
My nephew. Lord Ormund.

304
00:20:10.628 --> 00:20:13.839
musters his forces
to sally forth from Oldtown.

305
00:20:13.840 --> 00:20:15.257
They expect to march quickly.

306
00:20:15.258 --> 00:20:18.845
meeting little resistance.
until they reach the Riverlands.

307
00:20:18.970 --> 00:20:20.846
My letters to Rhaenyra.
Has there been any answer?

308
00:20:20.847 --> 00:20:23.598
An apology for her dead son?

309
00:20:23.599 --> 00:20:25.017
None. Your Grace.

310
00:20:25.143 --> 00:20:27.228
Between that and their
blockade of the Gullet.

311
00:20:27.353 --> 00:20:29.479
we must presume that
the princess has refused

312
00:20:29.480 --> 00:20:30.898
the offered terms.

313
00:20:31.023 --> 00:20:33.401
and that war is now inevitable.

314
00:20:33.526 --> 00:20:35.570
- Jaehaerys Targaryen: Na-na!
- Perhaps Your Grace might lend

315
00:20:35.695 --> 00:20:38.030
- his voice to our outreach...
- Tyland: Stop! Enough!

316
00:20:38.698 --> 00:20:40.949
...in hopes that new terms
might. might be negotiated.

317
00:20:40.950 --> 00:20:43.869
Release it at once!
Would someone please?

318
00:20:43.870 --> 00:20:47.039
Is the heir to the throne
bothering you. Tyland?

319
00:20:48.249 --> 00:20:51.919
No. No. no. not. not in
the least. Your Grace.

320
00:20:52.045 --> 00:20:54.504
Because I think he wants a ride.

321
00:20:54.505 --> 00:20:55.882
- Alicent: Your Grace.
- Tyland: Uh. a ride?

322
00:20:56.007 --> 00:20:57.340
A pony ride.

323
00:20:57.341 --> 00:20:58.842
Wouldn't that be fun. Jaehaerys?

324
00:20:58.843 --> 00:21:01.387
Should the Master of Coin
be your royal steed?

325
00:21:01.512 --> 00:21:03.264
(light laughter)

326
00:21:10.563 --> 00:21:12.106
Your Grace!

327
00:21:12.899 --> 00:21:15.234
There are important
matters to discuss...

328
00:21:16.569 --> 00:21:18.613
despite Sir Tyland's
interruptions.

329
00:21:20.073 --> 00:21:21.407
Aegon:
Very well.

330
00:21:22.033 --> 00:21:24.744
No time for amusements. Tyland.

331
00:21:26.079 --> 00:21:27.246
Your Grace.

332
00:21:28.081 --> 00:21:30.875
Aegon: Off you go.
Jaehaerys. Good boy.

333
00:21:33.252 --> 00:21:34.921
Where were we?
(clears throat)

334
00:21:36.130 --> 00:21:40.468
Rhaenyra's blockade has
placed King's Landing under strain.

335
00:21:40.593 --> 00:21:42.762
And those pressures
will multiply quickly.

336
00:21:42.887 --> 00:21:44.806
Well. we should've just killed
her when we had the chance.

337
00:21:44.931 --> 00:21:48.392
Regrettably. the opportunity
for surprise has been lost.

338
00:21:48.393 --> 00:21:52.605
and with it. the chance
to end this conflict quickly.

339
00:21:53.731 --> 00:21:55.732
We must play
the board before us.

340
00:21:55.733 --> 00:21:58.276
Tyland: If we are to break
the Sea Snake's blockade.

341
00:21:58.277 --> 00:22:01.029
we will need to bolster both the
Lannister and Hightower navies.

342
00:22:01.030 --> 00:22:03.783
We do have need
for a new Master of Ships.

343
00:22:03.908 --> 00:22:07.077
We could offer the title to
the young Lord Dalton Greyjoy.

344
00:22:07.078 --> 00:22:09.454
Aemond. What is
your business here?

345
00:22:09.455 --> 00:22:10.623
The king summoned me.

346
00:22:10.748 --> 00:22:12.290
You do not have a seat
at this council.

347
00:22:12.291 --> 00:22:15.711
Aemond is my closest
blood and our best sword.

348
00:22:15.712 --> 00:22:17.296
I welcome him.

349
00:22:17.922 --> 00:22:20.842
Path to King's Landing
is through the Riverlands.

350
00:22:20.967 --> 00:22:24.386
We must establish a
toehold there. at Harrenhal.

351
00:22:24.387 --> 00:22:26.596
Aegon: The Riverlords
will either declare for me.

352
00:22:26.597 --> 00:22:29.433
or they will meet Vhagar
and Sunfyre together.

353
00:22:29.434 --> 00:22:31.893
Ah. and-and we can burn
the blockade while we're at it.

354
00:22:31.894 --> 00:22:33.646
- Rhaenyra has dragons as well.
- Mine are bigger.

355
00:22:33.771 --> 00:22:36.440
If we lose the dragons to war.
there'll be no calling them back.

356
00:22:36.441 --> 00:22:37.941
- We must proceed cautiously.
- No.

357
00:22:37.942 --> 00:22:42.237
Fat. old Lord Tully will either
raise my banner or see his burn.

358
00:22:42.238 --> 00:22:44.365
We should fly to Riverrun.

359
00:22:44.699 --> 00:22:46.367
You are the king. Your Grace.

360
00:22:46.492 --> 00:22:47.784
You must not put
yourself at risk.

361
00:22:47.785 --> 00:22:50.579
And Vhagar is needed here
to deter Rhaenyra from attacking

362
00:22:50.580 --> 00:22:53.332
in retribution
for the death of her son.

363
00:22:54.167 --> 00:22:58.628
Errors were made in the hours
following King Viserys's death.

364
00:22:58.629 --> 00:23:01.049
We mustn't compound them.

365
00:23:02.341 --> 00:23:05.010
You've already demonstrated
your might. Your Grace.

366
00:23:05.011 --> 00:23:09.473
- We must now favor patience
and restraint. - (Aegon sighs)

367
00:23:09.474 --> 00:23:11.099
I send ravens by the hour.

368
00:23:11.100 --> 00:23:15.604
Many and more houses
will declare for you in time.

369
00:23:15.605 --> 00:23:19.025
History and precedent
will come to your side.

370
00:23:19.650 --> 00:23:22.361
- (birds chirping)
- (indistinct chatter)

371
00:23:26.657 --> 00:23:27.742
Good morrow. Your Grace.

372
00:23:27.867 --> 00:23:29.493
Good morrow. Lord Larys.

373
00:23:29.494 --> 00:23:31.412
I had come earlier
to have a word

374
00:23:31.537 --> 00:23:33.081
before the small
council convened.

375
00:23:33.206 --> 00:23:38.002
but your handmaiden said
that you were indisposed.

376
00:23:41.005 --> 00:23:43.257
What is it you wish to discuss?

377
00:23:45.051 --> 00:23:49.638
I have completed questioning
the whole of the castle staff.

378
00:23:49.639 --> 00:23:51.348
They produced rather
interesting details.

379
00:23:51.349 --> 00:23:56.354
but I am satisfied I have
exposed all who betrayed our trust.

380
00:23:58.231 --> 00:23:59.399
And what of them?

381
00:24:00.733 --> 00:24:03.069
They no longer breathe our air.

382
00:24:05.071 --> 00:24:08.908
I have chosen your
new staff personally.

383
00:24:13.746 --> 00:24:15.456
(door opens)

384
00:24:16.749 --> 00:24:18.418
(door closes)

385
00:24:27.093 --> 00:24:29.470
St... Gi-Give me that.

386
00:24:29.595 --> 00:24:30.930
maidservant:
Your Grace?

387
00:24:31.472 --> 00:24:33.474
(sighs)
Just leave me.

388
00:24:35.059 --> 00:24:37.270
Just le... Just le...
Just leave me.

389
00:24:40.940 --> 00:24:42.566
(door opens)

390
00:24:42.567 --> 00:24:45.444
(tense. pensive music playing)

391
00:24:45.445 --> 00:24:46.821
(door closes)

392
00:24:56.330 --> 00:24:57.623
♪

393
00:24:57.749 --> 00:24:59.459
(Syrax roars)

394
00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:16.851
♪

395
00:25:18.436 --> 00:25:19.854
(indistinct shouting)

396
00:25:19.979 --> 00:25:22.315
- It's a dragon wing!
- Let's have a look!

397
00:25:23.816 --> 00:25:25.985
- It's a wing.
- Who cares what it is.

398
00:25:26.694 --> 00:25:28.362
(yells)
Dragon!

399
00:25:28.488 --> 00:25:30.490
(crowd yelling)

400
00:25:31.491 --> 00:25:33.201
(Syrax roars)

401
00:25:35.369 --> 00:25:37.538
(yelling. panicking)

402
00:25:41.667 --> 00:25:43.336
(roars)

403
00:25:49.675 --> 00:25:52.845
(solemn music playing)

404
00:26:16.828 --> 00:26:18.787
♪

405
00:26:18.788 --> 00:26:20.540
(crying)

406
00:26:38.015 --> 00:26:40.226
(Syrax grumbling)

407
00:26:44.605 --> 00:26:47.608
♪

408
00:26:53.364 --> 00:26:54.949
(Syrax roars)

409
00:26:55.074 --> 00:26:58.119
Leon Estermont:
All hail King Aegon!

410
00:26:58.244 --> 00:27:00.704
"Aegon the Magnanimous."

411
00:27:00.705 --> 00:27:03.249
Second of His Name.
King of the Andals.

412
00:27:03.374 --> 00:27:05.584
and the Rhoynar.
and the First Men.

413
00:27:05.585 --> 00:27:08.963
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

414
00:27:09.088 --> 00:27:11.757
Hail King Aegon!

415
00:27:11.758 --> 00:27:13.551
"The Magnanimous"?

416
00:27:17.263 --> 00:27:18.264
Your Grace.

417
00:27:18.723 --> 00:27:22.226
Let's have the first
petition. my good Lord Hand.

418
00:27:23.770 --> 00:27:24.979
(grunts)

419
00:27:26.314 --> 00:27:28.149
(nervously) Good morrow.
my. uh. Your Grace.

420
00:27:28.274 --> 00:27:29.650
- (laughter)
- Aegon: It's alright.

421
00:27:29.776 --> 00:27:31.735
There's no reason to be nervous.

422
00:27:31.736 --> 00:27:32.861
What's your name?

423
00:27:32.862 --> 00:27:35.072
Gr... Uh. Jerard.
Your Grace.

424
00:27:35.073 --> 00:27:37.116
Good morrow. Jerard.

425
00:27:37.241 --> 00:27:39.827
And how might your king
be of service?

426
00:27:39.952 --> 00:27:42.370
'Tis my flock.

427
00:27:42.371 --> 00:27:46.334
Uh. a-a-a tenth
of them taken by...

428
00:27:48.127 --> 00:27:51.046
- the Crown on...
- (crowd murmuring)

429
00:27:51.047 --> 00:27:53.256
on the cusp of winter.

430
00:27:53.257 --> 00:27:56.469
- If I'd had the time to plan...
- We should return them.

431
00:27:59.347 --> 00:28:00.931
- Your Grace?
- Aegon: Well. you need

432
00:28:00.932 --> 00:28:02.432
your goats for the
winter. don't you?

433
00:28:02.433 --> 00:28:05.310
- Sheep. Your-Your Grace.
- Aegon: Sheep. even better.

434
00:28:05.311 --> 00:28:07.813
I shall make your
flock of sheep whole.

435
00:28:07.814 --> 00:28:09.439
(Jerard laughs)

436
00:28:09.440 --> 00:28:12.026
We already made a promise
to all the Crownlands

437
00:28:12.151 --> 00:28:14.362
that a tithing of livestock

438
00:28:14.487 --> 00:28:16.780
would be necessary
to sustain the dragons

439
00:28:16.781 --> 00:28:18.156
for their increased activity

440
00:28:18.157 --> 00:28:21.869
and. pray not.
eventual fighting.

441
00:28:21.994 --> 00:28:23.787
Right... Right.

442
00:28:23.788 --> 00:28:26.999
Perhaps we could just return
his sheep. He came all this way.

443
00:28:27.125 --> 00:28:29.544
If you return one herder's
sheep. Your Grace.

444
00:28:29.669 --> 00:28:32.129
you will soon find them
all at the foot of your throne

445
00:28:32.130 --> 00:28:34.589
expecting the same.

446
00:28:34.590 --> 00:28:36.008
They won't know.

447
00:28:36.134 --> 00:28:42.515
When the king speaks.
Your Grace. all hear it.

448
00:28:50.982 --> 00:28:53.901
After further thought.
I have decided that

449
00:28:54.026 --> 00:28:56.278
I cannot restore your sheep.

450
00:28:56.279 --> 00:28:57.696
If war were to break out.

451
00:28:57.697 --> 00:28:59.407
my dragons will require feed.

452
00:28:59.532 --> 00:29:02.284
- Bring the next.
- (crowd murmuring)

453
00:29:02.285 --> 00:29:06.037
guildmaster: Salts always
run scarce on the road to winter.

454
00:29:06.038 --> 00:29:07.039
Your Grace.

455
00:29:07.165 --> 00:29:08.957
We rely on ships from Essos

456
00:29:08.958 --> 00:29:10.376
for our supply.

457
00:29:10.501 --> 00:29:13.588
But now. with a blockade in
place and war threatening...

458
00:29:13.713 --> 00:29:15.839
Yeah. that treasonous
blockade won't last long.

459
00:29:15.840 --> 00:29:18.467
I plan to send Vhagar
to burn it to ash.

460
00:29:18.468 --> 00:29:19.718
Bring the next.

461
00:29:19.719 --> 00:29:21.846
(crowd murmuring)

462
00:29:23.765 --> 00:29:25.516
Hugh. Your Grace.

463
00:29:28.895 --> 00:29:30.228
The smiths are all proud

464
00:29:30.229 --> 00:29:32.690
to support Your Grace
against Rhaenyra.

465
00:29:36.444 --> 00:29:37.403
But?

466
00:29:37.528 --> 00:29:38.696
But...

467
00:29:40.239 --> 00:29:42.408
iron costs have grown.

468
00:29:43.201 --> 00:29:46.746
A lone scorpion
takes weeks to build.

469
00:29:47.371 --> 00:29:49.749
To put it simply.
we are struggling.

470
00:29:50.416 --> 00:29:54.920
If we could but have the Crown's
coin before we started work.

471
00:29:54.921 --> 00:29:56.713
it would bring great relief.

472
00:29:56.714 --> 00:30:00.426
Not just to me. but to all the
smiths serving your cause.

473
00:30:02.595 --> 00:30:03.763
(sighs)

474
00:30:04.931 --> 00:30:07.934
You shall be paid and paid well.

475
00:30:08.267 --> 00:30:10.435
My army cannot win a war
without your weapons.

476
00:30:10.436 --> 00:30:12.480
You should continue
their making.

477
00:30:12.772 --> 00:30:16.818
Our victory depends on
the efforts of the smallfolk.

478
00:30:19.153 --> 00:30:21.614
You have my most sincere
gratitude. Your Grace.

479
00:30:22.281 --> 00:30:24.951
Aegon: I'll hear
the next petition.

480
00:30:25.076 --> 00:30:27.286
(indistinct chatter)

481
00:30:31.791 --> 00:30:34.627
Larys Strong: Your Grace. it filled
my heart to see you on the Iron Throne.

482
00:30:34.752 --> 00:30:38.005
- (Aegon groans) - I was only a boy
when Jaehaerys last graced the seat.

483
00:30:38.131 --> 00:30:39.381
but you brought forth
memories of him.

484
00:30:39.382 --> 00:30:41.676
and you have such a deft
touch with the smallfolk.

485
00:30:41.801 --> 00:30:43.552
just as your father did.

486
00:30:43.553 --> 00:30:44.971
Thank you. my lord.

487
00:30:45.346 --> 00:30:47.765
I wonder. do you have a
moment for a quiet word?

488
00:30:53.646 --> 00:30:57.065
It is the Hand's won't to
keep a firm grip on things.

489
00:30:57.066 --> 00:30:59.234
Mm.

490
00:30:59.235 --> 00:31:01.487
He controlled your
father the same way.

491
00:31:02.822 --> 00:31:05.700
Viserys had a certain
reputation as being pliable.

492
00:31:05.825 --> 00:31:07.326
I am aware.

493
00:31:08.661 --> 00:31:11.079
I would think.
as we find ourselves

494
00:31:11.080 --> 00:31:13.290
standing within a hair's
breadth of war.

495
00:31:13.291 --> 00:31:16.502
that you would wish
to be viewed differently.

496
00:31:19.672 --> 00:31:20.922
How?

497
00:31:20.923 --> 00:31:22.717
Otto Hightower...

498
00:31:24.052 --> 00:31:27.180
was your father's Hand.
Your Grace.

499
00:31:43.696 --> 00:31:44.864
Daughter.

500
00:31:46.032 --> 00:31:48.743
I requested
an audience hours ago.

501
00:31:50.036 --> 00:31:53.873
There were many petitions.

502
00:31:56.375 --> 00:31:58.503
Alicent:
I find myself wondering...

503
00:31:59.379 --> 00:32:01.422
do we pursue the same end?

504
00:32:03.091 --> 00:32:06.886
I must admit. there are days
where I myself can't be sure.

505
00:32:08.429 --> 00:32:10.681
I shall tell you mine.

506
00:32:12.183 --> 00:32:13.517
It's victory.

507
00:32:13.518 --> 00:32:16.395
And how would you
define "victory"?

508
00:32:16.396 --> 00:32:18.355
Rhaenyra bending the knee

509
00:32:18.356 --> 00:32:21.275
and Aegon sitting
the Iron Throne. in peace.

510
00:32:21.901 --> 00:32:23.277
As Viserys wished.

511
00:32:23.403 --> 00:32:27.030
Well. if that's how you
describe it. then we are aligned.

512
00:32:27.031 --> 00:32:29.117
- Then be my ally.
- I am.

513
00:32:29.242 --> 00:32:30.743
An ally would not
repeatedly cut my legs

514
00:32:30.868 --> 00:32:32.787
from beneath me
at that table of men!

515
00:32:32.912 --> 00:32:36.540
- I sit there and I feel your anger.
- Frustration.

516
00:32:36.541 --> 00:32:38.917
These critical days
since Viserys's passing

517
00:32:38.918 --> 00:32:42.255
- haven't gone to plan.
- That's not my fault.

518
00:32:43.464 --> 00:32:46.426
My sons both see you
as the great example.

519
00:32:46.551 --> 00:32:47.885
The Hand to three kings.

520
00:32:49.429 --> 00:32:51.264
Aegon is ever-eager
to prove himself

521
00:32:51.389 --> 00:32:52.932
and Aemond...

522
00:32:54.392 --> 00:32:57.437
Aemond is angry.

523
00:32:57.562 --> 00:32:59.981
Rhaenyra's son took his eye
and was never punished for it.

524
00:33:00.106 --> 00:33:04.944
- What he did. however vicious...
- The caprice of youth.

525
00:33:08.990 --> 00:33:10.825
I could only hope.

526
00:33:10.950 --> 00:33:12.952
Aemond erred.

527
00:33:13.828 --> 00:33:17.372
But he is fiercely loyal.
He wishes to please.

528
00:33:17.373 --> 00:33:19.124
And Aegon still heeds me.

529
00:33:19.125 --> 00:33:20.835
In private. at least.

530
00:33:22.295 --> 00:33:23.587
But if you undermine my voice.

531
00:33:23.588 --> 00:33:25.464
both those boys
will grow deaf to it.

532
00:33:25.465 --> 00:33:28.760
(light music playing)

533
00:33:34.015 --> 00:33:35.975
I hadn't seen it that way.

534
00:33:36.434 --> 00:33:38.352
We only need to mind Aegon

535
00:33:38.478 --> 00:33:40.813
until the novelty
of rule is spent.

536
00:33:41.522 --> 00:33:44.608
Once he tires of it. you and I
can steer our cause to victory.

537
00:33:44.609 --> 00:33:47.361
A fine strategy. daughter.

538
00:33:47.945 --> 00:33:53.826
But you must accept that the path
to victory now is one of violence.

539
00:33:54.827 --> 00:33:56.496
I know it.

540
00:33:59.957 --> 00:34:02.502
But that does not mean
it must be wanton.

541
00:34:04.796 --> 00:34:05.797
No.

542
00:34:09.634 --> 00:34:12.845
(tense music playing)

543
00:34:19.185 --> 00:34:22.354
(indistinct shouting)

544
00:34:22.355 --> 00:34:24.857
solider (shouts):
Prepare to be boarded!

545
00:34:27.360 --> 00:34:30.405
By the order
of Lord Corlys Velaryon!

546
00:34:30.530 --> 00:34:33.156
Erryk Cargyll:
Search the hold for stowaways!

547
00:34:33.157 --> 00:34:35.410
♪

548
00:34:41.165 --> 00:34:43.167
(indistinct shouting)

549
00:34:51.551 --> 00:34:53.176
(goats bleating)

550
00:34:53.177 --> 00:34:55.430
(music fades out)

551
00:35:00.893 --> 00:35:01.894
You.

552
00:35:04.272 --> 00:35:07.692
When last we met.
there were two of you.

553
00:35:09.902 --> 00:35:11.027
"The White Worm."

554
00:35:11.028 --> 00:35:13.697
Mysaria: Did you think I
would wither in your absence?

555
00:35:13.698 --> 00:35:15.741
I did not think you
would flower a traitor.

556
00:35:15.742 --> 00:35:18.994
You speak of highborn
games. I am common-born.

557
00:35:18.995 --> 00:35:21.581
How long have you been
selling secrets to Otto Hightower?

558
00:35:21.706 --> 00:35:23.916
As long as he had gold
to pay for them.

559
00:35:25.960 --> 00:35:30.590
Who sent you fleeing from King's
Landing in such disrepair. hm?

560
00:35:31.758 --> 00:35:33.759
You put Aegon on the throne.

561
00:35:33.760 --> 00:35:35.844
That was the
Hightowers' conspiracy.

562
00:35:35.845 --> 00:35:38.473
I merely profited from
knowing Aegon's movements.

563
00:35:38.598 --> 00:35:39.932
But you delivered him.

564
00:35:40.058 --> 00:35:43.101
He would've returned home
eventually for gold and for respite.

565
00:35:43.102 --> 00:35:44.020
as he always does.

566
00:35:44.021 --> 00:35:47.106
I simply... simply sped
the business along.

567
00:35:47.231 --> 00:35:49.357
"Business" that ended with
the theft of the queen's throne

568
00:35:49.358 --> 00:35:50.567
and the murder of her son.

569
00:35:50.568 --> 00:35:52.527
You only blame me
because your true enemies

570
00:35:52.528 --> 00:35:54.489
are out of reach.

571
00:35:55.782 --> 00:35:57.240
My arrangement with the Hand

572
00:35:57.241 --> 00:35:58.700
was purely transactional.

573
00:35:58.701 --> 00:36:01.411
I held no loyalty to him.

574
00:36:01.412 --> 00:36:03.456
Certainly do not now.

575
00:36:03.915 --> 00:36:08.628
Otto Hightower was to me as I am
to your noble ilk. fodder to be cast off.

576
00:36:08.753 --> 00:36:10.379
What else do you
know of him? His plans?

577
00:36:10.380 --> 00:36:12.131
Little and less.

578
00:36:15.301 --> 00:36:18.679
I possess nothing
of value to you. Daemon.

579
00:36:29.315 --> 00:36:32.485
(gasps. breathes heavily)

580
00:36:36.656 --> 00:36:38.491
(door slams)

581
00:36:41.494 --> 00:36:42.870
Have her moved to the cells.

582
00:36:42.995 --> 00:36:45.832
She is to be treated
as a traitor to the crown.

583
00:36:48.501 --> 00:36:50.419
Erryk:
Forgive me. my prince...

584
00:36:50.420 --> 00:36:51.920
but the lady speaks the truth.

585
00:36:51.921 --> 00:36:55.341
- She was no agent of the Hightowers.
- What is it to you?

586
00:36:55.842 --> 00:36:58.593
- A matter of honor. - Was it honor
that made you stand by and watch

587
00:36:58.594 --> 00:37:01.347
as the Hightowers
usurped the throne?

588
00:37:01.472 --> 00:37:04.015
You and your traitorous twin.

589
00:37:04.016 --> 00:37:06.060
No. my prince.

590
00:37:07.353 --> 00:37:08.896
I'm shamed by it.

591
00:37:09.397 --> 00:37:11.524
That's why I abandoned
the Kingsguard.

592
00:37:11.649 --> 00:37:13.525
and my brother. and came here.

593
00:37:13.526 --> 00:37:16.111
I don't care.

594
00:37:16.112 --> 00:37:16.946
Aegon was in your grasp.

595
00:37:16.947 --> 00:37:18.865
You should've
killed him yourself.

596
00:37:18.990 --> 00:37:22.534
Arryk and I were named to
the Kingsguard at just 8 and 10.

597
00:37:22.535 --> 00:37:24.703
And we swore the same oath:

598
00:37:24.704 --> 00:37:27.165
to defend the whole
of the royal family.

599
00:37:28.207 --> 00:37:31.544
So what were we to do when
they turned against one another?

600
00:37:33.546 --> 00:37:35.715
(dragon roars)

601
00:37:40.553 --> 00:37:43.765
(tense music playing)

602
00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:51.731
♪

603
00:38:00.073 --> 00:38:04.326
Queen Rhaenyra Targaryen.
the First of Her Name.

604
00:38:04.327 --> 00:38:08.830
Queen of the Andals. and
the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

605
00:38:08.831 --> 00:38:13.085
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

606
00:38:13.086 --> 00:38:15.129
♪

607
00:38:18.925 --> 00:38:21.302
(whispers) Did you
find what you needed?

608
00:38:29.769 --> 00:38:32.730
Your council stands
at the ready. Your Grace.

609
00:38:36.609 --> 00:38:38.944
I will fly to Harrenhal
at your command

610
00:38:38.945 --> 00:38:41.239
and set our toehold
in the Riverlands.

611
00:38:41.989 --> 00:38:44.325
Your Grace. my lord
husband's blockade of the Gullet

612
00:38:44.450 --> 00:38:45.368
moves into place.

613
00:38:45.369 --> 00:38:46.576
All seaborne travel and trade

614
00:38:46.577 --> 00:38:48.955
to King's Landing
will soon be cut off.

615
00:38:49.080 --> 00:38:51.082
♪

616
00:38:54.836 --> 00:38:58.256
I want Aemond Targaryen.

617
00:38:59.257 --> 00:39:01.259
(music intensifies)

618
00:39:18.151 --> 00:39:20.153
♪

619
00:39:23.823 --> 00:39:25.992
(music fades out)

620
00:39:46.554 --> 00:39:49.139
In your years as a
merchant of gossip.

621
00:39:49.140 --> 00:39:51.808
you surely accumulated
spies within the Red Keep.

622
00:39:51.809 --> 00:39:54.019
Servants who knew
the comings and goings.

623
00:39:54.020 --> 00:39:55.979
Scheme with someone
else. Daemon.

624
00:39:55.980 --> 00:39:59.817
I was once in your
thrall. but no longer.

625
00:40:00.651 --> 00:40:02.528
A transaction. then.

626
00:40:03.071 --> 00:40:06.491
Your knowledge in
exchange for your freedom.

627
00:40:11.704 --> 00:40:14.082
(footsteps approaching)

628
00:40:19.045 --> 00:40:22.382
(light. solemn music playing)

629
00:40:33.726 --> 00:40:35.061
Your Grace.

630
00:40:36.270 --> 00:40:38.398
♪

631
00:40:38.523 --> 00:40:42.150
(emotional) Lady Jeyne
Arryn has pledged her support

632
00:40:42.151 --> 00:40:45.405
in exchange for a dragon
to guard the Vale.

633
00:40:47.949 --> 00:40:51.202
And Lord Cregan Stark...

634
00:40:53.913 --> 00:40:56.916
has promised 2.000 men...

635
00:41:02.296 --> 00:41:04.257
(both weeping)

636
00:41:04.382 --> 00:41:06.384
♪

637
00:41:12.598 --> 00:41:14.767
(door opens)

638
00:41:17.103 --> 00:41:19.105
♪

639
00:41:42.295 --> 00:41:43.963
Alyrie Florent.

640
00:41:44.464 --> 00:41:46.466
♪

641
00:42:02.774 --> 00:42:04.984
(music intensifies)

642
00:42:13.826 --> 00:42:15.995
Viserys Targaryen.

643
00:42:20.792 --> 00:42:23.002
♪

644
00:42:39.894 --> 00:42:42.146
♪

645
00:43:11.384 --> 00:43:15.555
(deep breath)
Lucerys Velaryon.

646
00:43:15.680 --> 00:43:17.682
♪

647
00:43:25.732 --> 00:43:27.900
(music fades out)

648
00:43:59.932 --> 00:44:01.892
(dog barking)

649
00:44:01.893 --> 00:44:04.645
(indistinct chatter)

650
00:44:04.771 --> 00:44:06.939
(Daemon whistles)

651
00:44:10.401 --> 00:44:11.486
A tribute.

652
00:44:11.611 --> 00:44:13.279
(coins jingle)

653
00:44:20.411 --> 00:44:21.829
Commander?

654
00:44:21.954 --> 00:44:24.123
Never gone for long.

655
00:44:25.583 --> 00:44:29.003
I'm told you bear a
mislike for the Hightowers.

656
00:44:30.129 --> 00:44:32.507
Fuck the Hightowers.

657
00:44:37.804 --> 00:44:39.471
Keep walking.

658
00:44:39.472 --> 00:44:41.516
(street chatter)

659
00:44:43.142 --> 00:44:45.311
Don't make trouble.

660
00:44:51.609 --> 00:44:52.984
(dog barks)

661
00:44:52.985 --> 00:44:54.444
Daemon Targaryen:
The White Worm said

662
00:44:54.445 --> 00:44:56.405
you're one of
Aegon's ratcatchers.

663
00:44:56.406 --> 00:45:00.451
You must be busy. That castle
positively crawls with them now.

664
00:45:01.494 --> 00:45:03.495
I heard the White
Worm were dead.

665
00:45:03.496 --> 00:45:05.831
Her ghost told me
you were a betting man.

666
00:45:05.832 --> 00:45:11.128
- Fighting pits?
- Dogs... and bones.

667
00:45:11.129 --> 00:45:13.172
How deep are your debts?

668
00:45:20.346 --> 00:45:22.181
I was also given to
understand that you possess

669
00:45:22.306 --> 00:45:24.474
a unique knowledge
of the Red Keep.

670
00:45:24.475 --> 00:45:26.352
Maegor's tunnels.

671
00:45:26.477 --> 00:45:28.563
Great big rat's nest. it is.

672
00:45:29.522 --> 00:45:32.817
I know them better than
the shape of my own cock.

673
00:45:35.194 --> 00:45:36.571
This is my friend.

674
00:45:37.697 --> 00:45:40.199
Tonight. he's going
to be your friend.

675
00:45:40.867 --> 00:45:44.203
You're to find and slay
the Prince Aemond Targaryen.

676
00:45:45.246 --> 00:45:47.873
He has silver hair and one eye.

677
00:45:47.874 --> 00:45:50.501
Should be easy enough to find.

678
00:45:52.045 --> 00:45:53.670
But I understand he's
quite good in a fight.

679
00:45:53.671 --> 00:45:55.590
You'll want to take caution.

680
00:45:57.091 --> 00:46:00.845
That's one half. You'll get
the other when it's done.

681
00:46:04.223 --> 00:46:06.392
(dog barking)

682
00:46:12.732 --> 00:46:14.067
Alright.

683
00:46:16.069 --> 00:46:17.862
What if we can't find him?

684
00:46:22.075 --> 00:46:25.869
We've wasted precious days
in this war of quills and ravens.

685
00:46:25.870 --> 00:46:28.748
Words are wind.

686
00:46:28.873 --> 00:46:31.083
You should be leading the van.

687
00:46:31.084 --> 00:46:33.543
and I should be flying
cover on Vhagar.

688
00:46:33.544 --> 00:46:36.922
No castle would dare to raise
Rhaenyra's banner against us.

689
00:46:36.923 --> 00:46:40.134
We would bring the whole of
the Crownlands to heel in weeks.

690
00:46:40.259 --> 00:46:43.053
Well. mayhaps we
could petition the king.

691
00:46:43.054 --> 00:46:46.307
privately. to send us out.

692
00:46:47.934 --> 00:46:49.684
Rosby and Stokeworth.

693
00:46:49.685 --> 00:46:53.188
small castles right in the
shadow of King's Landing.

694
00:46:53.189 --> 00:46:54.856
They would not want
us for enemies.

695
00:46:54.857 --> 00:46:57.276
We could add their
levies to our own.

696
00:46:58.277 --> 00:47:00.905
Our host growing as we advance.

697
00:47:03.074 --> 00:47:05.493
Uh. it is a canny scheme.

698
00:47:05.993 --> 00:47:07.453
But moot.

699
00:47:07.578 --> 00:47:10.498
My brother is hostage
to my grandsire and mother.

700
00:47:10.623 --> 00:47:14.127
and they tell him that a war
of dragons can yet be avoided.

701
00:47:14.252 --> 00:47:17.296
'Tis inevitable.
They must see that.

702
00:47:17.422 --> 00:47:19.757
Otto fears to upset
the order of things.

703
00:47:20.967 --> 00:47:23.136
And Alicent is simply...

704
00:47:24.095 --> 00:47:25.513
angry.

705
00:47:26.347 --> 00:47:29.725
- Angry?
- She blames me for starting this war

706
00:47:29.726 --> 00:47:34.188
after she plotted with my
father's council to usurp his throne.

707
00:47:35.606 --> 00:47:39.193
"Her Grace" speaks
with two tongues.

708
00:47:42.864 --> 00:47:45.116
She has a gentle heart.

709
00:47:45.616 --> 00:47:48.327
And Rhaenyra is
a cunning spider.

710
00:47:48.661 --> 00:47:52.831
Long ago. she drew
Alicent into her web...

711
00:47:52.832 --> 00:47:54.792
intoxicated her.

712
00:47:56.210 --> 00:47:58.337
It is not your mother's fault.

713
00:47:59.505 --> 00:48:01.883
She holds love for our enemy.

714
00:48:03.843 --> 00:48:05.845
That makes her a fool.

715
00:48:07.847 --> 00:48:09.681
(door opens)

716
00:48:09.682 --> 00:48:11.476
(footsteps approach)

717
00:48:22.528 --> 00:48:23.696
Lord Hand.

718
00:48:33.372 --> 00:48:35.290
Return to your post.
Lord Commander.

719
00:48:35.291 --> 00:48:37.710
I must have a word
with the prince.

720
00:48:49.764 --> 00:48:51.391
(door opens)

721
00:48:51.516 --> 00:48:53.226
It would concern me. grandson.

722
00:48:53.351 --> 00:48:54.727
if plans were being considered

723
00:48:54.852 --> 00:48:58.606
beyond the ears
of your king and his Hand.

724
00:48:59.190 --> 00:49:01.233
You have a zeal
to act. I understand.

725
00:49:01.234 --> 00:49:02.568
I was young once myself...

726
00:49:02.693 --> 00:49:05.905
I only wish to serve
my king and my house.

727
00:49:12.036 --> 00:49:13.454
You and Vhagar

728
00:49:13.579 --> 00:49:16.749
are the greatest single
power in the realm.

729
00:49:18.751 --> 00:49:22.547
If it wasn't obvious before.
it certainly is now.

730
00:49:27.260 --> 00:49:30.471
But there are many
pieces at play here...

731
00:49:31.431 --> 00:49:34.434
some of which you can't yet see.

732
00:49:35.143 --> 00:49:36.978
I promise you. Aemond.
you will have

733
00:49:37.103 --> 00:49:38.729
all the vengeance that you seek.

734
00:49:38.730 --> 00:49:42.567
but you must keep a
grip on your impulses.

735
00:49:45.111 --> 00:49:47.780
We both know that
your brother cannot.

736
00:49:50.950 --> 00:49:53.452
(street chatter)

737
00:49:53.453 --> 00:49:56.748
(tense music playing)

738
00:50:04.297 --> 00:50:06.674
- (dog whimpering)
- Cheese: Alright.

739
00:50:09.260 --> 00:50:11.471
♪

740
00:50:24.275 --> 00:50:26.486
♪

741
00:50:39.999 --> 00:50:41.375
Take that.

742
00:50:46.881 --> 00:50:48.633
Bring the dog.

743
00:50:49.300 --> 00:50:51.511
♪

744
00:51:13.074 --> 00:51:14.575
(laughter)

745
00:51:15.076 --> 00:51:17.536
Aegon: I need to be a
symbol for the smallfolk.

746
00:51:17.537 --> 00:51:19.414
- as well as the nobility.
- Cheese: Wait.

747
00:51:19.539 --> 00:51:21.206
speaker:
You could always be

748
00:51:21.207 --> 00:51:22.707
"Aegon the Strong."

749
00:51:22.708 --> 00:51:24.543
Aegon: My nephew's
already taken that one.

750
00:51:24.544 --> 00:51:26.378
- (laughter) - Leon: Well. which
would Your Grace prefer?

751
00:51:26.379 --> 00:51:28.256
- It's the king.
- Leon: To be loved or feared?

752
00:51:28.381 --> 00:51:29.631
Aegon:
I need to be both.

753
00:51:29.632 --> 00:51:32.051
My mother and grandsire

754
00:51:32.176 --> 00:51:34.594
mind me like some
helpless duckling.

755
00:51:34.595 --> 00:51:36.431
Oh. well. you're the king.

756
00:51:36.556 --> 00:51:37.724
Who gives a shit what they say?

757
00:51:37.849 --> 00:51:40.559
My brother. at least.
knows his place.

758
00:51:40.560 --> 00:51:42.644
He's as loyal as a hound.

759
00:51:42.645 --> 00:51:46.399
I can set him and his
dragon on my foes at will.

760
00:51:47.900 --> 00:51:49.902
- Cheese: Keep your eyes down.
- Aegon: I need a style that

761
00:51:50.027 --> 00:51:53.406
demonstrates power
and commands respect.

762
00:51:53.531 --> 00:51:56.409
Eh. no-no one knows
what "magnanimous" means.

763
00:51:56.534 --> 00:51:59.035
- (group laughs) - Leon: You could
be "Aegon the Generous" then.

764
00:51:59.036 --> 00:52:01.414
- That would charm the smallfolk.
- Aegon: I like that.

765
00:52:01.539 --> 00:52:02.790
Martyn Reyne:
Is there more strong wine?

766
00:52:02.915 --> 00:52:05.417
- Leon: "Aegon the Dragonheart."
- Aegon: Better.

767
00:52:05.418 --> 00:52:07.420
Leon: (laughs)
"Aegon the Dragoncock!"

768
00:52:07.545 --> 00:52:09.464
- Aegon: Yes. yes!
- (group laughs)

769
00:52:09.589 --> 00:52:11.757
Yeah. (laughs)
the untamable beast!

770
00:52:11.758 --> 00:52:13.801
♪

771
00:52:34.781 --> 00:52:37.115
How do we get upstairs?

772
00:52:37.116 --> 00:52:39.118
The royals live up there.

773
00:52:40.787 --> 00:52:41.746
Right.

774
00:52:41.747 --> 00:52:43.289
Well. it's off limits. it is.

775
00:52:43.790 --> 00:52:45.958
Different group of
ratcatchers work the upstairs.

776
00:52:46.084 --> 00:52:48.461
If we're to kill
a royal fucking prince.

777
00:52:48.586 --> 00:52:50.171
where do you think
we're gonna find him?

778
00:52:51.297 --> 00:52:53.256
I got you in the castle.

779
00:52:53.257 --> 00:52:54.967
I thought the rest was your bit.

780
00:52:55.093 --> 00:52:57.095
(Cheese grunting)

781
00:52:57.637 --> 00:52:59.347
I could end you right here.

782
00:52:59.472 --> 00:53:01.390
take the rest
of the gold meself.

783
00:53:01.391 --> 00:53:03.643
(Cheese panting)

784
00:53:04.352 --> 00:53:06.144
I know a way upstairs.

785
00:53:06.145 --> 00:53:09.147
I just don't know my way 'round.

786
00:53:09.148 --> 00:53:11.692
(grunts. panting)

787
00:53:11.818 --> 00:53:13.235
Show me.

788
00:53:13.236 --> 00:53:15.029
♪

789
00:53:15.154 --> 00:53:17.072
- Fuck off.
- (dog whimpers)

790
00:53:17.073 --> 00:53:19.158
(Cheese panting)

791
00:53:23.830 --> 00:53:24.997
This way.

792
00:53:27.166 --> 00:53:29.168
♪

793
00:53:45.727 --> 00:53:47.895
The royals live on this level.

794
00:53:48.020 --> 00:53:50.022
♪

795
00:53:52.483 --> 00:53:53.608
(grunts)

796
00:53:53.609 --> 00:53:55.862
(door creaking)

797
00:54:06.581 --> 00:54:08.332
No one's here.

798
00:54:08.833 --> 00:54:10.543
Blood:
We need to keep looking.

799
00:54:10.668 --> 00:54:13.211
I've told ya. I'm not
supposed to be up here.

800
00:54:13.212 --> 00:54:15.256
Did you not hear the prince?

801
00:54:16.215 --> 00:54:19.218
No head... no gold.

802
00:54:22.889 --> 00:54:24.891
♪

803
00:54:25.725 --> 00:54:28.227
- Set a trap.
- Huh?

804
00:54:28.728 --> 00:54:30.730
- Blood: For appearances.
- Oh.

805
00:54:31.022 --> 00:54:33.066
I'll search the next room.

806
00:54:38.071 --> 00:54:40.073
♪

807
00:54:43.576 --> 00:54:46.746
(storm blustering)

808
00:55:04.263 --> 00:55:06.181
(music softens)

809
00:55:06.182 --> 00:55:07.934
For the rats.

810
00:55:18.236 --> 00:55:20.238
♪

811
00:55:31.290 --> 00:55:33.292
(music intensifies)

812
00:55:36.462 --> 00:55:38.172
(thunder rumbling)

813
00:55:39.590 --> 00:55:42.135
- Cheese: Quiet.
- (clamoring)

814
00:55:42.969 --> 00:55:44.637
Quiet.

815
00:55:47.598 --> 00:55:49.809
Stay still.
(laughs)

816
00:55:51.936 --> 00:55:55.815
- (Cheese laughing)
- Who the fuck is she?

817
00:55:56.941 --> 00:55:59.152
She's the queen. she is.

818
00:55:59.485 --> 00:56:02.112
"A son for a son." he said.

819
00:56:02.113 --> 00:56:04.657
Well. does she look like
a fucking son to you?

820
00:56:04.782 --> 00:56:08.161
(laughing)
Over there.

821
00:56:08.619 --> 00:56:10.830
♪

822
00:56:17.503 --> 00:56:19.463
We need to get
our head and get out.

823
00:56:19.464 --> 00:56:21.716
- (grunting)
- Shh.

824
00:56:27.055 --> 00:56:30.140
They both look the same.
Which one's the boy?

825
00:56:30.141 --> 00:56:33.978
- Maybe that one.
- Well. look for a cock.

826
00:56:38.191 --> 00:56:39.484
The mother knows.

827
00:56:41.694 --> 00:56:43.779
Do anything but what I ask.

828
00:56:43.780 --> 00:56:47.033
and I'll bleed
the whole lot of ya.

829
00:56:49.035 --> 00:56:50.203
Shh.

830
00:56:53.539 --> 00:56:54.916
Which?

831
00:56:57.710 --> 00:56:59.921
I have a necklace.

832
00:57:01.589 --> 00:57:03.841
It's of great value.

833
00:57:04.217 --> 00:57:05.385
(gasps)

834
00:57:06.886 --> 00:57:08.888
That's not a son.

835
00:57:23.569 --> 00:57:24.779
N...

836
00:57:25.530 --> 00:57:27.240
(gasps)

837
00:57:32.370 --> 00:57:33.579
Wait.

838
00:57:34.414 --> 00:57:38.876
It's the other one. She's not gonna
give up the king's heir that easy.

839
00:57:48.261 --> 00:57:49.262
No.

840
00:57:50.805 --> 00:57:52.557
She's telling true.

841
00:57:53.641 --> 00:57:55.643
♪

842
00:57:56.102 --> 00:57:57.270
Blood:
Hold him down.

843
00:57:57.770 --> 00:57:59.939
(muffled screaming)

844
00:58:01.315 --> 00:58:02.316
No.

845
00:58:04.944 --> 00:58:07.447
- (blade slices)
- (grunting)

846
00:58:09.407 --> 00:58:11.325
(slicing flesh. bone)

847
00:58:11.451 --> 00:58:13.453
♪

848
00:58:15.788 --> 00:58:17.957
(Helaena muttering)

849
00:58:26.132 --> 00:58:28.134
♪

850
00:58:28.634 --> 00:58:30.303
(panting)

851
00:58:44.484 --> 00:58:45.985
(gasps)

852
00:58:50.323 --> 00:58:52.325
♪

853
00:59:01.834 --> 00:59:04.170
(Criston. Alicent panting)

854
00:59:05.838 --> 00:59:07.507
Alicent:
Helaena!

855
00:59:12.345 --> 00:59:14.013
What's happened?

856
00:59:16.015 --> 00:59:17.974
(music fades out)

857
00:59:17.975 --> 00:59:20.228
They killed the boy.

858
00:59:21.687 --> 00:59:23.856
(music fades in)

859
00:59:32.740 --> 00:59:34.992
♪

860
01:00:06.858 --> 01:00:09.068
♪

861
01:00:34.635 --> 01:00:36.637
(music fades out)

862
01:00:49.484 --> 01:00:51.611
- ♪ (ominous music plays)
- (dragon screeches)

863
01:00:51.736 --> 01:00:53.404
(children giggling)

864
01:00:53.780 --> 01:00:55.156
Aegon II Targaryen:
<i>I'll kill them!</i>

865
01:00:56.949 --> 01:00:57.909
(barks)

866
01:01:00.244 --> 01:01:01.788
I declare war!

867
01:01:08.920 --> 01:01:10.463
Rhaenyra Targaryen:
You have wounded me.

868
01:01:10.755 --> 01:01:13.007
Weakened my claim to the throne.

869
01:01:14.801 --> 01:01:16.177
<i>I cannot trust you. Daemon.</i>

870
01:01:16.677 --> 01:01:19.138
Alicent Hightower: <i>Rhaenyra's
supporters will believe what they wish.</i>

871
01:01:21.182 --> 01:01:22.642
<i>And so will Aegon's.</i>

872
01:01:23.768 --> 01:01:26.813
The significance of Viserys'
intentions died with him.

873
01:01:27.814 --> 01:01:29.524
Corlys Velaryon:
<i>There is a war brewing.</i>

874
01:01:30.316 --> 01:01:31.692
(dragon screeches)

875
01:01:31.818 --> 01:01:34.195
Aemond Targaryen: This war
will not be won with dragons alone

876
01:01:34.487 --> 01:01:37.031
but with dragons flying
behind armies of men.

877
01:01:37.156 --> 01:01:38.658
(Vhagar roars)

878
01:01:39.367 --> 01:01:41.327
Criston Cole: <i>The Riverlands
are the key to the war.</i>

879
01:01:41.452 --> 01:01:43.329
Harrenhal is the key
to the Riverlands.

880
01:01:44.497 --> 01:01:46.457
(caraxes roars)

881
01:01:46.874 --> 01:01:48.668
Daemon Targaryen:
Perhaps the presence of a dragon

882
01:01:48.876 --> 01:01:51.212
will sharpen minds
round these parts.

883
01:01:53.172 --> 01:01:55.049
Rhaenyra: <i>The path I walk
has never been trod.</i>

884
01:01:55.174 --> 01:01:55.842
(indistinct yelling)

885
01:01:56.342 --> 01:01:58.344
Mysaria: <i>There is more than
one way to fight a war.</i>

886
01:01:58.553 --> 01:01:59.720
(bell chimes)

887
01:01:59.721 --> 01:02:01.179
Aegon:
<i>I will not be seen as weak.</i>

888
01:02:01.180 --> 01:02:03.558
Otto Hightower: <i>You're
already seen as weak. Aegon.</i>

889
01:02:03.850 --> 01:02:05.893
Beware how you speak
to your king.

890
01:02:07.186 --> 01:02:08.062
(dragon screeches)

891
01:02:10.356 --> 01:02:14.026
Lord Broome: <i>We must seize the
hour and act before our enemy does.</i>

892
01:02:14.736 --> 01:02:17.321
Is there naught to be done
but to claw for power?

893
01:02:18.239 --> 01:02:20.699
♪ (music intensifies)

894
01:02:20.700 --> 01:02:22.702
What we must do is terrible.

895
01:02:24.495 --> 01:02:25.997
<i>Will you preside over it?</i>

896
01:02:27.707 --> 01:02:29.917
We must break the will
of our enemy.

897
01:02:31.544 --> 01:02:34.088
Daemon: <i>There will be no mercy!</i>

898
01:02:40.553 --> 01:02:42.179
♪ (music swells)

899
01:02:42.180 --> 01:02:43.181
(Vhagar roars)

900
01:02:44.515 --> 01:02:46.267
We have given the war
to the dragons.

901
01:02:48.102 --> 01:02:49.604
♪ (music concludes)

902
01:02:54.233 --> 01:02:56.611
speaker: <i>Duty is sacrifice.</i>

903
01:02:58.196 --> 01:03:00.114
<i>It eclipses all things.</i>

904
01:03:00.865 --> 01:03:02.075
<i>even blood.</i>

905
01:03:03.910 --> 01:03:04.952
In the making of season one.

906
01:03:05.078 --> 01:03:06.954
we knew half that season
is a prologue

907
01:03:07.080 --> 01:03:09.290
and half of it
is the first act of this war.

908
01:03:09.415 --> 01:03:11.626
<i>To have season one land
the way it did.</i>

909
01:03:11.751 --> 01:03:13.418
with a rabid audience.

910
01:03:13.419 --> 01:03:16.089
<i>fans of George and his books
the way I am.</i>

911
01:03:16.214 --> 01:03:17.381
<i>We were excited to get into it</i>

912
01:03:17.382 --> 01:03:20.301
because this is the juicy part
of the drama.

913
01:03:20.802 --> 01:03:22.470
♪ (somber music plays)

914
01:03:25.306 --> 01:03:28.559
speaker: <i>The North owes a
great duty to the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

915
01:03:29.060 --> 01:03:31.062
<i>one older than any oath.</i>

916
01:03:31.604 --> 01:03:34.106
Winterfell is the one place.
the one corner of this world

917
01:03:34.107 --> 01:03:36.608
where news of Luke's death
has not yet reached.

918
01:03:36.609 --> 01:03:41.405
and it is this hearkening back
to a simpler time.

919
01:03:41.406 --> 01:03:44.616
I wanted to go to a place
where we could experience that.

920
01:03:44.617 --> 01:03:45.493
if only briefly.

921
01:03:45.785 --> 01:03:48.329
and the North just felt
completely the right way to go.

922
01:03:48.663 --> 01:03:51.165
Ryan. when we did speak.
it really. really helped me out

923
01:03:51.290 --> 01:03:53.458
because we would have
conversations

924
01:03:53.459 --> 01:03:56.337
about how important
these negotiations are

925
01:03:56.462 --> 01:03:57.255
for Team Black

926
01:03:57.463 --> 01:04:00.006
<i>and the difference it makes
in the war.</i>

927
01:04:00.007 --> 01:04:02.969
War is coming to the whole
of the realm. My Lord.

928
01:04:03.511 --> 01:04:05.680
We cannot wage it without
the support of the North.

929
01:04:05.805 --> 01:04:07.348
Harry Collett: <i>Well.
it was all about history.</i>

930
01:04:07.473 --> 01:04:09.684
<i>There were pledges
that were made back in the day.</i>

931
01:04:09.809 --> 01:04:14.355
and Jace is sent to remind
Cregan Stark of those pledges.

932
01:04:14.689 --> 01:04:17.191
If your greybeards can fight.
the Queen will have them.

933
01:04:17.358 --> 01:04:20.653
They will fight hard.
like Northerners.

934
01:04:23.281 --> 01:04:25.783
Alan Taylor: <i>Rhaenyra heard
the news that Luke has died</i>

935
01:04:25.950 --> 01:04:27.200
on a mission
that she sent him on.

936
01:04:27.201 --> 01:04:28.494
so there's guilt involved.

937
01:04:28.619 --> 01:04:31.706
<i>And she's a mother
who's lost a son</i>

938
01:04:31.831 --> 01:04:32.623
and has to go through

939
01:04:32.624 --> 01:04:34.666
the sort of necessary
grieving process

940
01:04:34.667 --> 01:04:36.501
that Daemon. her husband.

941
01:04:36.502 --> 01:04:38.963
<i>can't really appreciate
or understand.</i>

942
01:04:39.213 --> 01:04:42.007
She goes and tries to make peace
with Luke's demise.

943
01:04:42.008 --> 01:04:43.051
but she cannot settle in it

944
01:04:43.176 --> 01:04:44.385
because it is
unsettled business.

945
01:04:44.510 --> 01:04:46.888
until part of Arrax
washes ashore.

946
01:04:47.055 --> 01:04:50.515
Going in search of evidence is

947
01:04:50.516 --> 01:04:52.309
<i>quite fundamentally important
to her.</i>

948
01:04:52.310 --> 01:04:56.688
<i>I guess one of the sort of
maddest things about death</i>

949
01:04:56.689 --> 01:04:58.191
<i>is that it seems
sort of impossible.</i>

950
01:04:58.524 --> 01:05:01.818
especially because really
the overriding feeling often is

951
01:05:01.819 --> 01:05:03.195
<i>you just sit with the absence.</i>

952
01:05:03.196 --> 01:05:06.074
<i>And so. anything that has. like.
a tangibility about it</i>

953
01:05:06.199 --> 01:05:07.741
I think is vitally important.

954
01:05:07.742 --> 01:05:11.079
<i>Her son's cloak.
the wing of his dragon.</i>

955
01:05:11.204 --> 01:05:12.704
I think it's devastating.

956
01:05:12.705 --> 01:05:17.085
<i>but I think it galvanizes
a vengeful feeling.</i>

957
01:05:17.418 --> 01:05:20.213
one that maybe she hasn't
paid so much mind to previously.

958
01:05:20.880 --> 01:05:23.091
(Syrax roars)

959
01:05:24.717 --> 01:05:27.095
Eve Best: <i>I think that Rhaenys
is probably one of the few people</i>

960
01:05:27.220 --> 01:05:28.929
<i>that Daemon knows
he can't mess with.</i>

961
01:05:28.930 --> 01:05:30.890
although I suspect
probably wants to.

962
01:05:32.392 --> 01:05:33.934
We're going to King's Landing.

963
01:05:33.935 --> 01:05:36.020
- To what end?
- Killing Vhagar.

964
01:05:36.396 --> 01:05:38.230
When those two meet.
it's kind of like

965
01:05:38.231 --> 01:05:42.944
a panther meets
a kind of electric eel.

966
01:05:43.069 --> 01:05:45.279
<i>Really dangerous combination.</i>

967
01:05:45.696 --> 01:05:49.075
He's essentially ready
to go to war and get payback.

968
01:05:49.534 --> 01:05:51.201
Ryan Condal: <i>It was nice
to throw those characters</i>

969
01:05:51.202 --> 01:05:52.870
<i>into conflict with one another.</i>

970
01:05:53.287 --> 01:05:55.872
I think you can tell
from even her demeanor

971
01:05:55.873 --> 01:05:57.625
the way Rhaenys
thinks of Daemon.

972
01:05:57.750 --> 01:05:59.626
Daemon believes that he's.
of course.

973
01:05:59.627 --> 01:06:00.461
completely in the right

974
01:06:00.753 --> 01:06:02.922
<i>and has the power
to order Rhaenys around.</i>

975
01:06:03.089 --> 01:06:04.257
Fly with me.

976
01:06:05.633 --> 01:06:06.718
It is a command.

977
01:06:06.968 --> 01:06:08.720
Would that you were the king.

978
01:06:09.470 --> 01:06:10.805
Aegon II Targaryen:
Where is Jaehaerys?

979
01:06:10.930 --> 01:06:12.306
What do you need of him?

980
01:06:12.598 --> 01:06:14.142
I'm taking him
to the Small Council.

981
01:06:14.767 --> 01:06:17.061
He'll be king one day.
He must begin his instruction.

982
01:06:17.270 --> 01:06:19.313
What if he does not want
to be king?

983
01:06:20.815 --> 01:06:21.649
(whispers) Where is he?

984
01:06:21.941 --> 01:06:23.442
One of the things I loved
about <i>Game of Thrones</i>

985
01:06:23.443 --> 01:06:24.568
was the character humor.

986
01:06:24.569 --> 01:06:26.320
And. you know.
we can spend a lot of time

987
01:06:26.446 --> 01:06:27.487
<i>being dour in this world.</i>

988
01:06:27.488 --> 01:06:28.947
<i>and it's so important
to have humor.</i>

989
01:06:28.948 --> 01:06:30.073
<i>And when I first saw</i>

990
01:06:30.074 --> 01:06:31.616
what Tom Glynn-Carney was doing
with Aegon.

991
01:06:31.617 --> 01:06:33.910
I thought. "He's finding humor
where I didn't know it existed."

992
01:06:33.911 --> 01:06:35.120
<i>And it's painful.</i>

993
01:06:35.121 --> 01:06:36.747
<i>a guy who's way in
over his head.</i>

994
01:06:36.748 --> 01:06:38.165
who really wants to do well

995
01:06:38.166 --> 01:06:40.000
but just can't make
a right move...

996
01:06:40.001 --> 01:06:42.128
(laughs)
...no matter what he does.

997
01:06:42.503 --> 01:06:44.672
speaker 2:
Aegon the Magnanimous.

998
01:06:44.839 --> 01:06:46.424
Hail King Aegon!

999
01:06:47.300 --> 01:06:48.676
The Magnanimous?

1000
01:06:50.511 --> 01:06:52.804
I think Aegon is
the kind of father

1001
01:06:52.805 --> 01:06:55.683
that encourages bad behavior
because he finds it funny.

1002
01:06:55.808 --> 01:06:56.809
<i>He loves his kids.</i>

1003
01:06:56.934 --> 01:06:58.310
<i>I have no doubt about that.</i>

1004
01:06:58.311 --> 01:06:59.644
<i>He loves his kids dearly.</i>

1005
01:06:59.645 --> 01:07:02.272
<i>But he's not one
to discipline them.</i>

1006
01:07:02.273 --> 01:07:04.192
If anything. he's. you know.

1007
01:07:04.317 --> 01:07:05.650
having competitions
with his children

1008
01:07:05.651 --> 01:07:07.862
to see who can be
the most rebellious.

1009
01:07:08.154 --> 01:07:09.654
<i>And Aegon often wins.</i>

1010
01:07:09.655 --> 01:07:10.615
He took my piece.

1011
01:07:10.823 --> 01:07:12.867
Is the heir to the throne
bothering you. Tyland?

1012
01:07:13.618 --> 01:07:15.536
We see him come into
a Small Council meeting

1013
01:07:15.661 --> 01:07:16.537
with Jaehaerys.

1014
01:07:16.662 --> 01:07:19.207
and. you know.
he's spurring him on.

1015
01:07:19.332 --> 01:07:22.793
He's wanting him to be
more of a... more of a rebel.

1016
01:07:22.794 --> 01:07:25.505
more of a nuisance.
just like his old man.

1017
01:07:25.630 --> 01:07:28.215
- I think he wants a ride.
- Alicent Hightower: Your Grace.

1018
01:07:28.216 --> 01:07:30.051
- Tyland Lannister: A ride?
- A pony ride.

1019
01:07:30.802 --> 01:07:32.177
Wouldn't that be fun. Jaehaerys?

1020
01:07:32.178 --> 01:07:34.555
Should the Master of Coin
be your royal steed?

1021
01:07:34.680 --> 01:07:36.014
(all chuckling)

1022
01:07:36.015 --> 01:07:37.516
It's meant to be
a moment of fun. a bit.

1023
01:07:37.517 --> 01:07:40.685
And yes. like Aegon brings
his four-year-old to work.

1024
01:07:40.686 --> 01:07:42.854
<i>But I think on a perhaps
nuanced character level.</i>

1025
01:07:42.855 --> 01:07:45.482
this is the thing that Viserys
never did for Aegon.

1026
01:07:45.483 --> 01:07:47.359
And Aegon did not study
at the feet of his father.

1027
01:07:47.360 --> 01:07:49.820
His father had his male heir
and then essentially said.

1028
01:07:49.821 --> 01:07:52.073
"Well. that box is ticked."
He was ill.

1029
01:07:52.365 --> 01:07:53.698
<i>I think he enjoyed having a son.</i>

1030
01:07:53.699 --> 01:07:56.034
<i>but didn't put in the work
the way he did with Rhaenyra</i>

1031
01:07:56.035 --> 01:07:57.160
<i>when he was a younger man.</i>

1032
01:07:57.161 --> 01:07:58.871
And I think Aegon resents that

1033
01:07:59.080 --> 01:08:00.539
and feels that
part of the reason

1034
01:08:00.540 --> 01:08:02.207
that he's not seen
as being suited

1035
01:08:02.208 --> 01:08:04.377
for the crown or the throne

1036
01:08:04.544 --> 01:08:07.422
is because he didn't get
that training from his father.

1037
01:08:07.547 --> 01:08:10.091
so now he's going to
make up for that tenfold

1038
01:08:10.216 --> 01:08:11.384
<i>with Jaehaerys.</i>

1039
01:08:13.928 --> 01:08:16.096
Alan: <i>Alicent's been
in a marriage that was loving.</i>

1040
01:08:16.097 --> 01:08:20.058
but not exactly romantic
or physical for quite some time.

1041
01:08:20.059 --> 01:08:21.893
Cole has got a lot of issues.

1042
01:08:21.894 --> 01:08:23.353
<i>One thing I love
about the character</i>

1043
01:08:23.354 --> 01:08:25.106
<i>is that he is a knight
in shining armor</i>

1044
01:08:25.231 --> 01:08:26.232
and sort of classically handsome

1045
01:08:26.566 --> 01:08:28.692
and probably the most
messed up person in the story

1046
01:08:28.693 --> 01:08:29.569
in many ways.

1047
01:08:29.861 --> 01:08:31.612
<i>You know. clinging to notions
of purity and duty</i>

1048
01:08:31.738 --> 01:08:34.365
<i>and just flagrantly
breaking them left and right.</i>

1049
01:08:34.741 --> 01:08:36.074
So. there's a lot
of complex things

1050
01:08:36.075 --> 01:08:37.909
driving the moves
closer and closer

1051
01:08:37.910 --> 01:08:39.120
between Alicent and Cole.

1052
01:08:39.412 --> 01:08:40.579
And it takes a leap forward.

1053
01:08:40.580 --> 01:08:41.789
<i>But nothing is simple with them.</i>

1054
01:08:41.914 --> 01:08:43.791
<i>so for every leap forward.
there's a push back.</i>

1055
01:08:44.125 --> 01:08:46.711
We cannot... again.

1056
01:08:46.961 --> 01:08:48.712
Alan: <i>There's a lot
of wonderful tension there.</i>

1057
01:08:48.713 --> 01:08:51.882
I mean. I think there's love.
but there's a lot of mess too.

1058
01:08:51.883 --> 01:08:52.967
(laughs)

1059
01:08:53.384 --> 01:08:54.885
- Your Grace.
- Good day.

1060
01:08:54.886 --> 01:08:56.387
Fabien Frankel:
<i>I think. ultimately.</i>

1061
01:08:56.596 --> 01:09:01.768
they're two very lost people
in a pretty unforgiving world.

1062
01:09:02.101 --> 01:09:04.436
And I think there's always been.

1063
01:09:04.437 --> 01:09:06.481
<i>you know.
since the very first episode.</i>

1064
01:09:06.606 --> 01:09:08.398
<i>Alicent. you know.
had her eye on Criston Cole.</i>

1065
01:09:08.399 --> 01:09:10.400
<i>And then she was a young lady.</i>

1066
01:09:10.401 --> 01:09:13.780
<i>and now she's
the Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

1067
01:09:14.280 --> 01:09:16.782
Olivia Cooke: <i>It's paramount
that she keeps it a secret</i>

1068
01:09:16.783 --> 01:09:19.993
because not only
would her respect

1069
01:09:19.994 --> 01:09:22.120
completely disintegrate.

1070
01:09:22.121 --> 01:09:24.581
<i>but her stay in the castle.</i>

1071
01:09:24.582 --> 01:09:27.334
And Aegon is so unpredictable.
Who knows what he would do

1072
01:09:27.335 --> 01:09:31.171
if he found out
that his mother was having sex

1073
01:09:31.172 --> 01:09:33.341
with his
Commander of the Kingsguard?

1074
01:09:33.466 --> 01:09:35.258
I mean. not only is it
an embarrassment.

1075
01:09:35.259 --> 01:09:38.930
<i>it would bring deep. deep shame.</i>

1076
01:09:42.475 --> 01:09:45.144
I want Aemond Targaryen.

1077
01:09:46.521 --> 01:09:49.190
Rhaenyra has literally one line
in the first episode.

1078
01:09:49.315 --> 01:09:50.483
and the one line she says.

1079
01:09:50.817 --> 01:09:52.985
Daemon takes
as pulling the trigger.

1080
01:09:53.152 --> 01:09:55.822
In our first episode.
we see him unleash something

1081
01:09:55.947 --> 01:09:58.324
that is sort of famous in
the lore of <i>House of the Dragon.</i>

1082
01:09:58.491 --> 01:10:00.535
<i>a nasty event that he triggers.</i>

1083
01:10:00.993 --> 01:10:04.705
When Rhaenyra declares
that she wants Aemond.

1084
01:10:04.831 --> 01:10:09.711
<i>I think it's an admission
of a possibly shameful desire.</i>

1085
01:10:09.836 --> 01:10:12.839
<i>and I think that admission
is made directly to Daemon.</i>

1086
01:10:13.005 --> 01:10:16.007
I think it's also an admission
of their similarity.

1087
01:10:16.008 --> 01:10:19.011
<i>She sort of discloses
another way in which</i>

1088
01:10:19.137 --> 01:10:21.848
<i>they actually share a darkness.</i>

1089
01:10:22.515 --> 01:10:25.392
"I want Aemond Targaryen"
becomes the battle cry

1090
01:10:25.393 --> 01:10:27.686
that then resonates
across the entire season

1091
01:10:27.687 --> 01:10:30.355
because that is
the next domino to fall

1092
01:10:30.356 --> 01:10:32.983
<i>in this back and forth
that sets in motion</i>

1093
01:10:32.984 --> 01:10:34.902
<i>a horrible attack
and counterattack</i>

1094
01:10:35.027 --> 01:10:35.820
<i>that continues.</i>

1095
01:10:36.154 --> 01:10:38.531
<i>and the atrocities grow worse
and worse as they go.</i>

1096
01:10:39.031 --> 01:10:40.699
Alan: <i>In our story.
it's Mysaria.</i>

1097
01:10:40.700 --> 01:10:42.868
who has got her tentacles into
every part of King's Landing.

1098
01:10:42.869 --> 01:10:45.036
who is able to provide
the connections

1099
01:10:45.037 --> 01:10:47.414
for Daemon to exact revenge.

1100
01:10:47.415 --> 01:10:49.040
<i>I think it really is a big deal
for the fans</i>

1101
01:10:49.041 --> 01:10:50.418
<i>because it keeps
getting referred to.</i>

1102
01:10:50.543 --> 01:10:52.502
And I don't know
the characters' actual names.

1103
01:10:52.503 --> 01:10:54.755
They're forever in lore
as Blood and Cheese.

1104
01:10:54.756 --> 01:10:57.174
- (laughing)
- Who the fuck is she?

1105
01:10:57.175 --> 01:10:58.717
She's the Queen. she is.

1106
01:10:58.718 --> 01:11:00.677
"A son for a son." he said.

1107
01:11:00.678 --> 01:11:02.220
The boldest thing that
I think we did there

1108
01:11:02.221 --> 01:11:04.932
was decide to give the last
ten minutes of the episode

1109
01:11:05.058 --> 01:11:07.560
over to these two characters
that we have never met before

1110
01:11:07.685 --> 01:11:10.437
<i>and rely on them to take us
through the end of the story</i>

1111
01:11:10.438 --> 01:11:12.064
and to see. hopefully.

1112
01:11:12.065 --> 01:11:14.066
as they go deeper and deeper
into the Red Keep

1113
01:11:14.067 --> 01:11:15.943
and as we're spending more
and more screen time on them

1114
01:11:16.069 --> 01:11:18.446
that something horrible
is going to happen in there.

1115
01:11:18.571 --> 01:11:20.906
and knowing that you're watching
<i>Game of Thrones</i>

1116
01:11:20.907 --> 01:11:23.743
and you don't know what is going
to come for you from where.

1117
01:11:23.951 --> 01:11:25.869
<i>And seeing that play out
hopefully is the fun</i>

1118
01:11:25.870 --> 01:11:28.790
and the horror for the audience
that's yet to come.

1119
01:11:29.082 --> 01:11:31.292
♪ (music swells) ♪

1120
01:11:31.417 --> 01:11:32.627
(muffled yelp)

1121
01:11:33.628 --> 01:11:35.213
♪ (music concludes)

1121
01:11:36.305 --> 01:12:36.393
